  <section class="evo-faq" id="faq" aria-labelledby="evo-faq-h2">
    <div class="ic-container">
      <div class="evo-section-head">
        <span class="evo-badge">FAQ</span>
        <h2 id="evo-faq-h2">Frequently Asked Questions About IT Support in Perth</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="evo-faq__grid">
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>What is business IT support in Perth?</h4>
          <p>Business IT support means having someone you can call when your technology stops working — and someone who proactively keeps it running in the first place. EvoTech Digital is a Perth-based IT provider helping small businesses with remote support, on-site visits, Microsoft 365, cybersecurity basics, and hardware procurement — all handled by one person who knows your setup.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>How does EvoTech handle support requests?</h4>
          <p>Contact EvoTech by phone or email during business hours. Most issues are resolved remotely on the same business day. On-site visits for hardware or network work are scheduled by appointment across the Perth metro area. For businesses on a monthly support agreement, requests receive priority handling.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>What does IT support cost for a Perth business?</h4>
          <p>EvoTech offers both one-off support (charged hourly) and monthly support agreements (flat-rate per month based on the scope of services). Monthly agreements are better value for businesses that need regular help. Contact EvoTech for a straightforward quote based on your actual requirements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>What's the difference between monthly support and break-fix?</h4>
          <p>Break-fix means you only call when something breaks — you pay per incident and get no proactive maintenance. A monthly support agreement means patch management, system monitoring, and security hygiene are handled on a regular schedule, reducing the likelihood of things breaking in the first place. Most businesses find the predictable cost and fewer surprises worth the switch.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>Does EvoTech provide on-site IT support across Perth?</h4>
          <p>Yes. On-site support is available across the Perth metropolitan area by appointment. EvoTech visits businesses for hardware setup, network installations, equipment replacement, and any issue that can't be resolved remotely. If you're unsure whether your issue needs a site visit, get in touch and we'll advise.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>Can EvoTech support Microsoft 365 and cloud services?</h4>
          <p>Yes. EvoTech provides Microsoft 365 setup, migration, and ongoing management — including Teams, SharePoint, Exchange, OneDrive, and user account management. With Microsoft's Perth data centre now live, businesses using Azure benefit from better local performance and Australian data residency.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>Is EvoTech suitable for very small businesses?</h4>
          <p>EvoTech Digital is specifically focused on small Perth businesses — from sole traders and startups to established SMBs with a small team. If you've been managing IT yourself or relying on a friend for help, EvoTech can take that off your plate properly, without the cost of a large IT firm.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evo-faq-item">
          <h4>What happens if I have an IT issue outside business hours?</h4>
          <p>EvoTech is a small business and operates during standard Perth business hours. For businesses that need after-hours coverage, this is something to discuss upfront — EvoTech can advise on monitoring tools and self-service options that reduce the impact of out-of-hours issues, and discuss what escalation options are appropriate for your situation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

